---
Every event dict produced by EventDetector must contain exactly these keys:
  city (str), event_type (str), timestamp (datetime), summary (str),
  reason (str), metrics (dict)

event_type must be one of these exact strings (no others):
  sudden_temp_drop, sudden_temp_rise, city_anomaly, feels_like_gap,
  dangerous_wind, wind_shift, heavy_precipitation, precip_streak,
  weather_code_severity, cross_city_divergence

summary is one sentence, human-readable, no jargon.
reason explains WHY the detector fired — include threshold and actual value.
metrics must include the numeric values that triggered the event.

Example of a correct event:
{
  "city": "Ottawa",
  "event_type": "feels_like_gap",
  "timestamp": "2024-01-15T14:00:00",
  "summary": "Ottawa feels 11°C colder than actual temperature.",
  "reason": "Apparent temperature (-6°C) deviates 11°C from actual (5°C), exceeding the 8°C threshold.",
  "metrics": {"temperature": 5.0, "apparent_temperature": -6.0, "gap": 11.0}
}
